'''Luka Vušković''' (born 24 February 2007) is a Croatian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]] for {{German football updater|Hamburg}} club [[Hamburger SV]], on loan from {{English football updater|TottenhH}} club [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]], and the [[Croatia national football team|Croatia national team]].

== Club career ==
===Hajduk Split===
Born in [[Split, Croatia|Split]], Vušković progressed through the [[HNK Hajduk Split Reserves and Academy|academy]] of the local side [[HNK Hajduk Split|Hajduk Split]], becoming the youngest Croatian to play, and to score, in the [[UEFA Youth League]].<ref name=Verma>{{cite news |last=Verma |first=Keshava |date=22 March 2023 |title=Who is Luka Vuskovic – The next big thing in Croatian Football? |url=https://khelnow.com/football/2023-03-world-football-who-is-luka-vuskovic |work=Khel Now |location=New Delhi |access-date=23 March 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/rusi-sve-rekorde-luka-ce-biti-najbolji-vuskovic-u-hajduku-864606|title=Ruši sve rekorde: 'Luka će biti najbolji Vušković u Hajduku'|trans-title=Breaking all records: 'Luka will be the best Vušković in Hajduk'|first1=Tomislav|last1=Gabelić|first2=Mato|last2=Galić|date=6 October 2022|accessdate=10 November 2022|website=24sata.hr|language=Croatian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://abcportal.info/novosti/sport/hajduk-slavio-i-dobio-rekordera-luka-vuskovic-postao-najmladi-hrvat-u-juniorskoj-ligi|title=Hajduk slavio i dobio rekordera: Luka Vušković postao najmlađi Hrvat u juniorskoj Ligi prvaka|trans-title=Hajduk celebrated and got a record holder: Luka Vušković became the youngest Croat in the Junior Champions League|date=13 September 2022|accessdate=10 November 2022|website=abcportal.info|language=Croatian}}</ref>

He made his unofficial debut at 15, playing in a friendly against [[NK Urania Baška Voda|Urania]] in September 2022.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bild.de/sport/fussball/hsv/hsv-mit-15-bei-den-profis-jetzt-startet-der-bruder-von-mario-vuskovic-durch-81437700.bild.html|title=Jetzt startet der Vuskovic-Bruder durch|trans-title=Now the Vuskovic brother is taking off|first=Babak|last=Milani|date=26 September 2022|accessdate=10 November 2022|website=bild.de|language=German}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/vjecni-trenutak-dragulja-bilih-za-hajduk-zaigrao-15-godisnjak-862474|title=Vječni trenutak dragulja 'bilih': Za Hajduk zaigrao 15-godišnjak|trans-title=The eternal moment of the jewel of 'the former': A 15-year-old played for Hajduk|first1=Tomislav|last1=Gabelić|first2=Boris|last2=Trifunović|date=25 September 2022|accessdate=10 November 2022|website=24sata.hr|language=Croatian}}</ref> On 16 December 2022, he scored in a 4–3 friendly victory over the German side [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hajduk.hr/vijest/prijateljska-utakmica-hajduk--schalke-04-4-3/15458|title=Prijateljska Utakmica: Hajduk - Schalke 04 4:3|trans-title=Friendly Match: Hajduk - Schalke 04 4:3|date=16 December 2022|accessdate=24 December 2022|website=hajduk.hr|language=Croatian}}</ref>

On 26 February 2023, two days after his sixteenth birthday, Vušković made his professional debut, starting and playing 90 minutes in a [[2022–23 Croatian Football League|league]] derby match against [[Dinamo Zagreb]], which ended in a 4–0 loss for his side.<ref>{{Cite web |date=26 February 2023 |title=Eto nam i Luke! Vušković sa 16 godina i 2 dana ispisuje povijest Hajduka i hrvatskog nogometa |url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/eto-nam-i-luke-vuskovic-sa-16-godina-i-2-dana-ispisuje-povijest-hajduka-i-hrvatskog-nogometa-894104 |access-date=26 February 2023 |website=24sata |language=hr}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite web |date=26 February 2023 |title=MLADI LUKA VUŠKOVIĆ ZA POVIJEST! Veliki talent Hajduka krenuo od prve minute u derbiju |url=https://www.dnevno.hr/sport/mladi-luka-vuskovic-za-povijest-veliki-talent-hajduka-krece-od-prve-minute-u-derbiju-2103161/ |access-date=26 February 2023 |website=Dnevno.hr |language=hr |last1=Šojat |first1=Gordan }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=26 February 2023 |title=Dinamo ponizio Hajduk: Poigravao se sa Splićanima. Bez problema pobijedio 4:0 - Teleskop |url=https://teleskop.hr/hrvatska/dinamo-ponizio-hajduk-poigravao-se-sa-splicanima-bez-problema-pobijedio-40/ |access-date=26 February 2023 |website=Teleskop |language=hr}}</ref> In the process, he became the youngest player in the Croatian top flight, together with [[Marko Dabro]];<ref name=":0" /> he also became the youngest player to ever feature in an [[Eternal derby (Croatia)|Eternal derby]] game, surpassing [[Josip Bašić]].<ref name=":0" />

On 2 March 2023, Vušković scored the opening goal in Hajduk's 2–1 win over [[NK Osijek|Osijek]] in the quarter-finals of the [[2022–23 Croatian Football Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Osijek: Osijek - Hajduk 1:2 |url=https://hajduk.hr/vijest/osijek-hajduk-1-2/15643 |access-date=2023-03-01 |website=hajduk.hr |language=hr}}</ref> Scoring at 16 years and 5 days old, he became the youngest goalscorer in the history of Hajduk Split, in official matches.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Luka Vušković: Lijep je osjećaj zabiti gol u ovakvoj utakmici, posvećujem ga bratu |url=https://hajduk.hr/vijest/luka-vuskovic-lijep-je-osjecaj-zabiti-gol-u-ovakvoj-utakmici-posvecujem-ga-bratu/15645 |access-date=2023-03-01 |website=hajduk.hr |language=hr}}</ref>

====Loan to Radomiak Radom====
On 31 January 2024, after failing to make an appearance for Hajduk since the start of the [[2023–24 HNK Hajduk Split season|2023–24 season]], Vušković joined Polish [[Ekstraklasa]] club [[Radomiak Radom]] on a six-month loan.<ref>{{cite web |title=Luka Vušković wypożyczony do Radomiaka! |url=https://radomiak.pl/artykul-5848-luka_vuskovic_wypozyczony_do_radomiaka_.html |publisher=[[Radomiak Radom]] |access-date=31 January 2024 |language=pl |date=31 January 2024}}</ref> He made his first-team – and [[Ekstraklasa]] – debut on 10 February 2024, coming on as a 64th-minute [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Mike Cestor]] in a 0–6 away loss against [[KS Cracovia|Cracovia]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=PKO Ekstraklasa: Cracovia 6-0 Radomiak |url=http://www.90minut.pl/news/330/news3304840-PKO-Ekstraklasa-Cracovia-6-0-Radomiak.html |access-date=2024-02-10 |website=www.90minut.pl}}</ref> Six days later, Vušković received his first start for the club in a 0–4 home loss against [[Pogoń Szczecin]]. He returned to Hajduk at the end of the season.<ref>{{cite web |title=Dziękujemy za grę dla Radomiaka! |url=https://radomiak.pl/artykul-6089-dziekujemy_za_gre_dla_radomiaka_.html |publisher=Radomiak Radom |access-date=3 July 2024 |language=pl |date=3 July 2024}}</ref>

====Loan to Westerlo====
On 9 July 2024, he was loaned to [[K.V.C. Westerlo|Westerlo]] in the [[Belgian Pro League]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Welkom Luka |url=https://kvcwesterlo.be/2024/07/09/welkom-luka/ |website=kvcwesterlo.be |publisher=KVC Westerlo |access-date=9 July 2024 |language=nl |date=9 July 2024}}</ref> Even as a centre-back, he scored seven league goals throughout the course of the season and won the 2024 Belgian Pro League goal of the season award for his goal against [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]].<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.express.co.uk/sport/football/2018948/tottenham-transfer-news-saka-vuskovic-goals| title='I'm a defender joining Tottenham - I have more league goals than Bukayo Saka this season'| publisher=Daily Express| last=Sunderland| first=Tom| date=25 February 2025| access-date=16 August 2025}}</ref>

===Tottenham Hotspur===
On 25 September 2023, Vušković reached an agreement with [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] about joining the [[Premier League]] club in 2025, in a deal which will run until 2030.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-09-25 |title=Vuskovic to join Spurs |url=https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/2023/september/vuskovic-to-join-spurs/ |access-date=2023-09-25 |website=[[Tottenham Hotspur]] |language=en}}</ref> The deal was reported to be worth around £12 million.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4852654/2023/09/11/tottenham-luka-vuskovic-transfers/ |title=Tottenham close to signing 16-year-old Luka Vuskovic from Hajduk Split |publisher=The Athletic |date=11 September 2023 }}</ref> Vušković joined Tottenham in July 2025 for their [[2025–26 Tottenham Hotspur F.C. season#Pre-season and friendlies|2025–26 preseason]], where he got a goal and an assist in his unofficial debut for Tottenham in a 2–0 friendly win against [[Reading F.C.|Reading]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Reading 0-2 Tottenham: Thomas Frank era begins with a win as Will Lankshear and Luka Vuskovic score|date=19 July 2025|publisher=Sky Sports|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/13397495/reading-0-2-tottenham-thomas-frank-era-begins-with-a-win-as-will-lankshear-and-luka-vuskovic-score|access-date=14 November 2025}}</ref> Tottenham wanted to keep Vušković for the season as a backup player, where he was an unused substitute in the [[2025 UEFA Super Cup|UEFA Super Cup final]] and Tottenham's first 2 Premier League matches of the season against [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] and [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]],<ref>{{cite web|title=PSG vs Tottenham LIVE: European Champions beat Spurs on penalties to win Super Cup|date=13 August 2025|publisher=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cjr1l8epz02t#Line-ups|access-date=14 November 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Tottenham Hotspur 3-0 Burnley: Richarlison double helps Spurs to impressive win|date=16 August 2025|publisher=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cx2xx252d1xt#Line-ups|access-date=14 November 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Manchester City vs Tottenham Hotspur match report|date=23 August 2025|publisher=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cd0d3zjj8g3t#Line-ups|access-date=14 November 2025}}</ref> but Vušković requested to go out on loan as he wanted to get regular game time.<ref>{{cite web|last=Soriano|first=Joe|title='Wanted to keep me' - Tottenham have to love that star man fought to leave|date=24 October 2025|publisher=Yahoo! Sports|url=https://sports.yahoo.com/article/wanted-keep-tottenham-love-star-120007398.html?guccounter=1|access-date=14 November 2025}}</ref>

====Loan to Hamburger SV====
On 29 August 2025, Vušković moved on loan to [[Bundesliga]] club [[Hamburger SV]] in Germany, joining his brother [[Mario Vušković|Mario]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Hamburger SV|url=https://www.hsv.de/en/news/hsv-sign-luka-vuskovic-on-loan|title=HSV sign Luka Vuskovic on loan|date=29 August 2025|access-date=4 September 2025}}</ref> Vušković scored his first goal for Hamburg on 20 September in a 2–1 league win over [[1. FC Heidenheim|Heidenheim]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Hamburger SV vs Heidenheim: Bundesliga stats & head-to-head|date=20 September 2025|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cdx2v09yyq6t#Line-ups|publisher=BBC Sport|access-date=7 December 2025}}</ref> and on 28 September, he became the first player to win 18 aerial duels in one match in Europe’s top 5 leagues in 5 years whilst playing against [[1. FC Union Berlin|Union Berlin]], and won Bundesliga Rookie of the Month for September and October.<ref>{{cite web|title=Luka Vušković named Bundesliga Rookie of the Month for October|date=31 October 2025|publisher=Bundesliga|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/rookie-of-the-month-2025-26-vote-winners-sorare-34232|access-date=23 November 2025}}</ref> On 7 December, Vušković scored his second goal for Hamburg in a 3–2 win against [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Hamburger SV vs Werder Bremen: Bundesliga stats & head-to-head|date=7 December 2025|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/ce862790rlrt|publisher=BBC Sport|access-date=7 December 2025}}</ref> Vušković was named in the [[2025–26 Bundesliga]] Team of the Season.<ref name=":1">{{cite news |date=29 April 2026 |title=Check out the EA SPORTS FC 26 Bundesliga Team of the Season! |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/team-of-the-season-ea-sports-fc-26-voting-36810 |access-date=6 May 2026 |publisher=Bundesliga}}</ref> He concluded the season with six goals in 28 Bundesliga appearances, finishing as the league's highest-scoring defender and recording the best duel success rate in the division at 69.1%.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hsv.de/en/news/luka-vuskovics-unforgettable-year-at-the-volkspark|title=Luka Vuskovic’s unforgettable year at the Volkspark|publisher=Hamburger SV|date=21 May 2026}}</ref>

== International career ==
Vušković represented Croatia at youth international level,<ref name=wf/> On 9 June 2025, he debuted for the senior national team in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification|World Cup qualifying]] match against the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic]] that ended in a 5–1 victory for Croatia, replacing [[Duje Ćaleta-Car]] in the 88th minute.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Luka Vušković becomes third-youngest debutant in Croatia's national team history|url=https://en.nogomania.com/read/Luka-Vuskovic-becomes-third-youngest-debutant-in-Croatia-s-national-team-history#goog_rewarded|website=Nogomania|date=10 June 2025}}</ref> Vušković made his first start for the Croatia national team on 14 November 2025 in a 3–1 win against [[Faroe Islands national football team|the Faroe Islands]], which qualified Croatia for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Croatia 3-1 Faroe Islands: Croatia qualify for World Cup and end Faroes hopes|date=14 November 2025|publisher=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cev1p10gv41t#Line-ups|access-date=23 November 2025}}</ref> On 26 March 2026, he scored his first goal for senior team in a friendly match against Colombia.

== Personal life ==

Hailing from a footballing family, Vušković's father, [[Danijel Vušković|Danijel]], formerly played for Hajduk Split, and now serves as a coach for the youth team.<ref name=family>{{cite web|url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/dinastija-vuskovic-pape-dida-i-pradida-bili-su-stoperi-hajduka-862481|title=Dinastija Vušković: Pape, dida i pradida bili su stoperi Hajduka|trans-title=The Vušković dynasty: Pope, grandfather and great-grandfather were Hajduk stoppers|first1=Tomislav|last1=Gabelić|first2=Boris|last2=Trifunović|date=25 September 2022|accessdate=10 November 2022|website=24sata.hr|language=Croatian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://slobodnadalmacija.hr/sport/hajduk/luka-vuskovic-puni-16-godina-dan-prije-derbija-s-dinamom-zaigra-li-postat-ce-najmladi-debitant-u-povijesti-hajduka-i-hnl-a-1231376|title=Luka Vušković puni 16 godina dan prije derbija s Dinamom. Zaigra li, postat će najmlađi debitant u povijesti Hajduka i HNL-a|trans-title=Luka Vušković turns 16 the day before the derby with Dinamo. If he plays, he will become the youngest debutant in the history of Hajduk and HNL|first=Slaven|last=Alfirević|date=11 October 2022|accessdate=10 November 2022|website=slobodnadalmacija.hr|language=Croatian}}</ref> His grandfather, [[Mario Vušković (footballer, born 1953)|Mario]], played for the youth teams of Hajduk Split during the tenure of [[Tomislav Ivić]], and went on to forge a footballing career in the Netherlands.<ref name=family/> His great-grandfather, Marko, also played for Hajduk Split during [[World War II in Yugoslavia|World War II]], and went on to work as a club executive.<ref name=family/>

More recently, his brother, also named [[Mario Vušković|Mario]], left Hajduk Split for Germany, where he joined [[Hamburger SV]].<ref name=family/> He was banned for 2 years for [[Doping in sport|doping]] on 30 March 2023.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.reuters.com/lifestyle/sports/hamburg-defender-vuskovic-banned-two-years-doping-german-fa-2023-03-30/ | title=Hamburg defender Vuskovic banned for two years for doping-German FA | date=2023-03-30 | publisher=[[Reuters]]}}</ref> The ban was later extended to November 2026.

His cousins, [[Moreno Vušković|Moreno]] and Vito, are also footballers, as was their father, Ronald.<ref name="family" />

== Style of play ==

Standing at {{Convert|1.93|m|ft|abbr=on}}, Vušković holds an advantage among young players due to his height. He is notable for his positioning and ability to contemplate the opposition's plans and act accordingly. His heading abilities are also characteristic, making him a danger to the opposition during set pieces. For this reason, he is among the top scorers among young players, even though he plays as a centre-back. His imposing physique also gives him an advantage as a defender, while his quick thinking and ball distribution help facilitate attacks. Jacek Kulig, a scouting expert, stated that Vušković has no significant weaknesses.<ref name=Verma/>

Vušković's style of play has been compared to that of the Spanish international [[Gerard Piqué]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/nogomet/video-cudesni-hajdukovac-luka-vuskovic-zabio-gol-sa-svoje-polovice---746080.html|title=VIDEO Sjajni hajdukovac Luka Vušković zabio gol sa svoje polovice|trans-title=VIDEO Great striker Luka Vušković scored a goal from his own half|date=9 October 2022|accessdate=10 November 2022|website=[[Gol.hr]]|language=Croatian}}</ref> while Vušković himself named [[Joško Gvardiol]] as his football role model.<ref>{{cite web | title=Vušković o hrvatskom reprezentativcu: 'On je životinja! To nikad nisam vidio' | website=Tportal.hr | date=2025-06-19 | access-date=2025-06-20 | url=https://www.tportal.hr/sport/clanak/vuskovic-o-hrvatskom-reprezentativcu-on-je-zivotinja-to-nikad-nisam-vidio-20250619 | language=hr | author=A. H.}}</ref>

